  "title": "Field Engineer (base salary & allowance provided)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: Field Network EngineerLocation: Singapore</strong></p><p><strong>We are partnering with a leading telecom client </strong>to hire a Field Network Engineer as part of<strong> </strong>Enterprise Field Operation Team plays a key role in supporting enterprise services and are responsible in link testing, installation, testing and maintaining equipment’s such as routers, switches, convertors and Telecommunication equipment’s for the enterprise services. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>·        To support field activities both on-site & off-site, such as configuration & installation, equipment management, also submission of site access requests, assignment of orders to engineers or vendors.</p><p>·        Liase with stakeholders (PM, AM, Teir3, vendors etc ) to support link testing & activation and ensure end-to-end connectivity.</p><p>·        Configure routing protocols (e.g. OSPF, BGP, static routes) on routers as per network design.</p><p>·        Conduct acceptance tests: RFC2544, BER tests, OTDR tests, signal level measurements, ping/trace tests</p><p>·        Validation circuit design with test result to determine compliance with the design/contract specifications </p><p>·        Document test results and sign off with customer/operations.</p><p>·        Troubleshoot service outages across transmission layers (L1/L2) and IP/MPLS layers (L3).</p><p>·        Diagnose hardware faults in routers, switches, fiber, power units, and transmission nodes.</p><p>·        Restore degraded links or alarms (LOS, LOF, AIS, low signal, link flap).</p><p>·        Liase with NOC or vendor when required.</p><p>·        Tracking of order closure & status</p><p>·        Prepare site reports, installation logs, maintenance checklists.</p><p>·        Update CPE inventory records in system </p><p>·        Record fault history and recommendations.</p><p>·        Verification of vendor’s claims</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree/Diploma/ITE holder in Computer Science, Electrical / Electronics Engineering, Telecommunication Engineering</li><li>At least 1-2 years of experience in supporting enterprise network  </li><li>Experience in configuring routers /firewall/switches/convertors</li><li>Ability in performing 24x7 standby duties (standby and call out allowances provided)</li><li>Possess a Class 3 driving Licenses is essential </li><li>Strong communications skills with stakeholders at all levels</li><li>Basic soft skills in Microsoft office</li><li>Fresh Graduates are welcome to apply. </li></ul><p><br /><em>UEN: 202329526G</em>  <br /><em>EA Licence:23S2061</em></p>",
